My meme

Personally, I prefer green, so I use image_ Blank created a picture with a green background.

In addition, my favorite animal is puppy, so I selected cute puppy pictures from the network and loaded them into the project. I also added the text description A lovely dog!.

# Import {magick} package
library(magick)

# Use image_blank to create a picture with a length of 100, a width of 100, and a background color of green, named meme1
meme1 <- image_blank(496,330,"green")  %>%
  image_annotate(meme2, "A green picture", location = geometry_point(150,150), size = 32)
meme1
image_write(meme1, "my_meme1.png")

# Set the path of the picture to be read
memeImg_Path = c("https://nimg.ws.126.net/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdingyue.ws.126.net%2F2020%2F1231%2Fb8161777p00qm7gba0089c000ds0096m.png&thumbnail=660x2147483647&quality=80&type=jpg")

# Use image_read to read pictures
meme2 <- image_read(memeImg_Path)
meme2
meme2 %>% image_write("my_meme2.png")

# Use image_annotate to add text to the picture at the position of 150,150
meme3 <- image_annotate(meme2, "A lovely dog!", location = geometry_point(150,150), size = 32)
meme3
meme3 %>% image_write("my_meme3.png")

# Use image_append to vertically combine the above three pictures into one picture
meme_imgs = c(meme1, meme2, meme3)
meme4 <- image_append(meme_imgs, TRUE)
meme4 %>% image_write("my_meme4.png")

My animated GIF

On the basis of the file meme. R, I added more effect changes to the dog image. For example, use image_Annotate adds text to the picture;

Use image_Append combines multiple pictures into one;

Use image_Average Change the color of the picture;

Use image_Scale Enlarge the picture;Use image_ Crop crop pictures;

Use image multiple times_ Rotate rotates the image at different angles.

Finally, use image for multiple images_ Animate Composite animation with 10 frames;
